	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83141><span id=Scholar>Ellon the Charming</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>37 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Cailiph, I would recommend seeking out an Erudite Cultural Tailor.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Imbued Steelsilk armor is INCREDIBLE SK armor.  I'm a 52nd level Erudite Enchanter, and I crafted an entire set of Imbued Steelsilk for my 26th level SK.<br><br>I realize you don't have the funds available to a higher level player, but if you could find an Erudite with high tailoring skill (over 140, to be on the safe side, although Imbued trivs at 109), make friends with that person and see if you can work out a way for him to make the armor.<br><br>It takes some work to get this armor, but it's far better than any other SK armor out there.<br><br>It requires:<br>Terrorantula Silks - unlikely find for a lower level player, however, you may just ask for some, since nobody has any clue what these silks are used for.<br>Clear Mana - horribly expensive, requires 4 Rubies and a Poison vial.<br>Imbued Amber - easy enough to get.<br>Proper pattern - also easy to get.<br><br>In reality, the trickiest part is getting the Terrorantula silks.  However, just going around and asking for some is a good tactic.  A lot of people pick them up while killing the Ancient Cyclops in South Ro.  You could also find some on merchants every once in a while.<br><br>Anyhow, hope this helps.  It's not something you can look forward to immediately at level 9, but as you advance in levels and save your money, I'm sure you'll be able to get yourself a few pieces of this incredible armor.<br><br>I suggest looking through Allakhazam and looking at the stats for this.  It's Imbued Steelsilk Armor (breastplate, gauntlets, etc. etc.)<br><br>The absolute best value piece in this set is perhaps the Gauntlets or the Shoulders, if you're looking for the quick fix.  Flayed Skin Boots are just slightly weaker than the Imbued Steelskin Boots.  The Greaves, Breastplate and Cloak all require 6(!!!) silks in order to craft, so they may be the harder ones to get, but there are a lot of options for melee classes in those 3 slots.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>D'Tox</td></td></tr>
