	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>278 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.03]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Some suggestions, but remember server prices very alot so you may get more or less for your Plat.<br><br>First I'd get a Ry'Gorr Battlemail, 18 AC + STR wt 1 (I think, might be less) so it's great for what you need.&nbsp;&nbsp;On my server they are going for about 500pp.<br><br>Then I'd get a magic 1hs and shield.  Even a Velium Longsword is nice so you can kill Wisps and Ghouls.  But if you can find a Frozen Longsword (about 10pp) and a Cracked Darkwood Shield (about 100pp) you will be ready to go for a few more levels.  If you are willing to learn a new weapon, get a Backjack or Wraithbone Warhammer, both are nice 1hb wepons, light, fast and cheap.  The Wraithbone Warhammer adds 2 STR and INT so it has extra bonus but the Blackjack is faster so you'll learn 1hb faster.<br><br>Lastly I'd recommend you fill in some slots with + STR items.  An Orc Fang Necklace adds 5 STR and goes for 50pp or so, also Jagged Bands (rings) add 3 STR each and cost about the same.  Also the Blood Stained Mantle goes for about 50pp and gives +STR as well (and it's still used into the high 40's for the sv magic).<br><br>If you are still having weight issues look to replace all the remaining bronze with Tizmak Armor.  It has the same AC and weighs about half.  It looks bad on most races but it's functional.<br><br>For a wish list I'd start saving for a Hero Bracer, Spider Fur Collar, belt and Cloak, and Treeweave (25AC +10 STR BP).<br><br>Good luck, you should enjoy the challenge of the Erudite SK.  Don't let anyone convince you to restart for another Race, you have everything you need to get to lvl 60.<br><br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 55 DE Revenant</p>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 62 DE Gravelord<br>Have Axe, will travel</td></td></tr>
